         <c id="ref68" level="series">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Additional material</unittitle>
               <unitid>Accession 2010-M-040</unitid>
               <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">Circa 1998-circa 2000</unitdate>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_a56caf9bdabe4a59ee4bf4e7656e3068">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>This accession comprises two databases, one containing information concerning foreign workers in the Adam Opel AG plant in Rüsselsheim, Germany during the World War II era, and the other containing evaluative records concerning documents and articles relating to General Motors' acquisition, ownership, management, loss of effective control, write-off, and reacquisition of Adam Opel AG during the period from 1929 through the early 1950s. These databases were created sometime betweeen 1998 and 2000 by a team of researchers directed by Professor Henry A. Turner of Yale University.</p>
            </scopecontent>
            <relatedmaterial id="aspace_217d7efaaefd416b70b31988daced69a">
               <head>Related Archival Materials note</head>
               <p>See also: <ref actuate="onrequest" show="replace" target="ref15">General Motors Documents Relating to World War II Corporate Activities in Europe (MS 1799).</ref> Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>
            </relatedmaterial>
            <bibliography id="aspace_630e54b4088fe18bbf18bcc728fe58da">
               <head>Bibliography</head>
               <p>
                  <emph render="italic">Related Publication Note:</emph> The databases were created during the course of research that resulted in the following publication: Turner, Henry Ashby, Jr. <title render="italic">
                     <part>General Motors and the Nazis: The Struggle for Control of Opel, Europe's Biggest Carmaker</part>
                  </title>. New Haven: Yale University Press, 2005.</p>
            </bibliography>
            <c id="ref69" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Arbeiter database</unittitle>
                  <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">Circa 1998-circa 2000</unitdate>
                  <physdesc id="aspace_396833129eb08cfbaec38cab34a42e09">1 computer file (Microsoft Access)</physdesc>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_ca49b4501a3245577c70effb3453f6cf">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>This database contains information on foreign workers at the Adam Opel AG plan in Rüsselsheim, Germany, during the early 1930s through World War II. This information was extracted from Ostarbeiter (Eastern worker) savings books and personnel records maintained by Opel.</p>
               </scopecontent>
               <accessrestrict id="aspace_cb1e32a99f59b3cb36c938ac68ddabe8">
                  <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
                  <p>The computer files are unprocessed and are in a physical state that requires staff intervention before use. Researchers wishing to request access should email mssa.assist@yale.edu. The staff intervention may take up to 10 business days.</p>
               </accessrestrict>
            </c>
